# =================================================
# ChatWebApp Frontend Environment Configuration
# =================================================

# Backend API Configuration
# --------------------------
# Full URL to the backend API (must include /api/v1 path)
# Development (local backend)
VITE_API_HOST=http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1

# Production examples:
# VITE_API_HOST=https://api.yourdomain.com/api/v1
# VITE_API_HOST=https://your-backend-domain.com/api/v1

# Important Notes
# ---------------
# 1. Only variables prefixed with VITE_ are exposed to the client
# 2. After changing this file, restart the dev server (npm run dev)
# 3. WebSocket connections are automatically derived from VITE_API_HOST
#    (http:// -> ws://, https:// -> wss://)
# 4. Ensure the backend is running and accessible at the specified URL
# 5. CORS must be properly configured on the backend for this origin

# Development Tips
# ----------------
# - Use 127.0.0.1 instead of localhost to avoid DNS issues
# - Make sure the port matches your backend server (default: 8000)
# - The /api/v1 path is required as part of the API base URL

